node.text: Everyone wants the feeling of freedom, but procrastination can feel like you are caged and can't find the key. We all get stuck in patterns, and the patterns become habits. Procrastination is the same thing.  Procrastination is an action (or non-action) – and it does not define you. Why? It is a habit, that is a behavior pattern that can be changed into a new pattern

We live in a comparison culture, and it’s easy to forget one essential piece of information. You are a miracle. node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Project Happiness on August 06, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'As I look back on my life, I realize that every time was thought being rejected from something good was actually being redirected to something better. Steve Maraboli @projecthappiness_org ecthappiness_org'.

node.text:
Did not being chosen for a job you desired even lead you to a better one? Did a breakup ever lead you to a better relationship? Sometimes we have rigid expectations of the path we are “supposed to be” on. Yet, life may have other ideas. 

Don't fight what comes up; instead, you can choose to go with the flow and see where it takes you. Life is usually pointing you in the direction of something greater. Examine yourself and realize that you already possess all you require to achieve. Don't fixate on what went wrong because you are already actually being guided to something better. Instead of dwelling too long in disappointment, ask yourself these  2 questions:

1. What have I learned from this situation? 

2.How can it make me stronger?

Trust and stay open; then you will notice the better things that are on the way.

Give a Heart if you have ever experienced this.
#projecthappiness
#freedomfriday
#positivity
#quoteoftheday

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Project Happiness on August 05, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'that Everything irritates us about others to us can lead an understanding of ourselves. Carl Jung @projecthappiness_org'.

node.text:
Everything that bothers you comes up for a reason. You have to ask yourself ‘why’ to get to the bottom of it. 

Consider that often what you don’t like or accept in yourself is precisely what irritates you in the other person. For example, if you witnessed a lot of anger when you were a child,  you may be uncomfortable with expressing anger now. So unconsciously, you may attract a partner who has anger issues, which can bother you a lot! Why do we do that? The relationship unknowingly becomes the playing ground for resolving old hurts.

And just as we have many emotions, we all have many sides, many different parts of ourselves. Some we can own (the “good “ parts), and some we disown or don’t want to admit. (These are sometimes called the split-off parts of ourselves or the shadow side.) 
 
What to do? Being willing to accept (and have compassion for) that part of yourself and skillfully learning, for example,  how to acknowledge and express your own anger, is a most positive step. 

AWARENESS -> SELF-ACCEPTANCE -> GROWTH

The emotions you are most uncomfortable with, may be the keys to helping you integrate all parts of yourself.  so you can finally feel at home in your own skin.
#projecthappiness
#thoughtfulthursday
#positivity
#quoteoftheday

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Project Happiness on August 04, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'I would rather adjust my life to your absence than adjust my boundaries to accommodate disrespect. your haren Civil @projecthappiness_org'.

node.text:
Sometimes growth does not happen in tandem, and when one person changes, it can disrupt the familiar rhythms of a relationship. That doesn’t have to spell disaster. It can be an invitation for the other person to grow as well. 

The only thing is... that is not in your control. If things devolve to full on stress and disrespect, it is important to know what works for you, and what crosses a line. There are times when taking a stand for yourself is the only way to move forward. Though, you cannot control how the other person will react, you can make choices that give you (and potentially both of you) the room to grow. 

 Remember you have a well of inner strength inside of you; realize how valuable and wonderful you are, and stay true to you. You alone have the power to decide who deserves your heart.

“No one can make you feel inferior without your consent.” - Eleanor Roosevelt
#projecthappiness
#wellnesswednesday
#positivity
#quoteoftheday

May be an image of flower and text that says '"SOMETIMES YOU HAVE TO LET GO OF THE PICTURE OF WHAT YOU CONG LIFE WOULD BE LIKE AND LEARN TO FIND JOY IN THE STORY YOU ARE ACTUALLY LIVING." RACHEL MARIE MARTIN @PROJECTHAPPINESS_ORG'.

node.text:
Life is full of unexpected twists and turns; we really never know what will happen next. And when we think that life takes a turn for the worse, it’s so easy to succumb to disappointment and unhappiness. These are the moments when we are so preoccupied with the past and future that we forget to live in the here and now.

When we let go of the life we imagined, we can welcome whatever life brings us with open arms; which means we can focus on the things that we already have and the lives we already lead instead of on what we haven’t acquired or achieved.

When we let go of the image we imagined, life often opens far better doors for us to discover who we really are.

“Happiness is letting go of what you think your life is supposed to look like and celebrating it for everything that it is.” ~Mandy Hale

What is one thing you are willing to let go of?
#projecthappiness
#gratituesday
#positivity

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Project Happiness on August 02, 2021. May be an image of sky and text that says '"In any given momen we have w options: to step forward into growth step back into safety." or Abraham Maslow @projecthappiness Abrahamaslowphaplnss_ org'.

node.text:
As children, we need safety - it is a matter of survival. We depend on our parents or caregivers for everything. In the best of situations, they were there. Unfortunately, in many, though trying the best they could, they were not emotionally available. This quest for safety doesn’t end as adults, so the allure of safety, or staying in a familiar discomfort is very strong. That, however does not promote growth. 

There comes a time when we realize that in order to be fully alive and know our potential, we have to try new things, and  break out of the comfort zone. Like pants that we have outgrown, we no longer fit into old ways of showing up. We have become bigger than our ego might have us believe. So if you feel stuck in a mindset that is telling you that “you are not enough,” know that this is your ego trying to keep you small. 

This is the time to trust in your true nature, to step into growth, and discover what you are made of. Sure, fear and doubts will arise, but by taking action, you are proving to yourself that you are capable of change and growth. And the ultimate safety is not through others, but solidly within yourself.

CHALLENGE: In the next 24 hours, try one thing you have been considering. Take one step into an area you want to grow. Send one text to someone who matters. Get out of your comfort zone, and into your true self.
#projecthappiness
#mindfulmonday
#positivity
#quoteoftheday

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Project Happiness on August 01, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'YOU WILL NEVER BE HAPPY IF YOU ARE CONSTANTLY JUDGING YOURSELF. GIVE YOURSELF SOME GRACE @PROJECTHAPPINESS_ORG'.

node.text:
It's not always simple to be fair to yourself. Overthinking is a temptation that most of us, especially sensitive people, wish we could avoid. When fear shows up as self-judgment, it poisons the present moment.

Most of the time, judgement occurs subconsciously, hurting your own happiness, and the relationships you have with yourself and others.

When it comes down to it, judging yourself is the ego’s way of keeping you where you are. You notice things you don't like about yourself, your life, and the people in it.

Constant judgement might seem like you're in conflict with yourself, even convincing yourself that you should be someone other than who you are.

If you want to work on judging yourself less, concentrate on your ability to be more aware. Don’t stop pushing yourself to grow new skills, but do your best to do so with more love and compassion towards yourself.  Rather than constantly putting yourself down and overanalyzing every step you take, take a gentler approach.

Are you ready to do this?
#projecthappiness
#soulsunday
#positivity
#quoteoftheday

node.text:
There are so many reasons to be proud of someone. Maybe your partner got a promotion or accomplished something at work. Perhaps a friend of yours created a lovely work of art. Maybe someone you know who has been dealing with an illness is keeping a good attitude and staying proactive. 

Noticing their efforts is good, but telling them your feelings is even better. Tell someone you are proud of them. It builds your bond and shows that you care. Besides, everyone likes to be seen and acknowledged. Do that for all your relationships if you can: friends, partners, family, colleagues...even for yourself.  Tag one person (or a few!) and tell you are proud of them.
#projecthappiness
#positivity
#socialsaturday

node.text:
Though life throws all sorts of challenges our way, they do not have to define us. Even if you had a hard patch, it doesn’t mean that you are destined for a hard life. When you are open to possibilities, possibilities open up for you.

A few things to remember:

1. What matters more than the events in our lives is how we interpret them. Did they crush us, or did we learn something valuable?

2. Everything is evolving. Just like nature has seasons, we do too. Nothing stays static.

3. We have the power to choose whether to respond to conflict as our best selves, or simply react according to old patterns,

“Everything can be taken from a man but one thing: the last of the human freedoms—to choose one’s attitude in any given set of circumstances, to choose one’s own way.” - Viktor Frankl
#projecthappiness
#freedomfriday
#positivity
#quoteoftheday

Say Yes if Agree
You have your own timeline. You don’t need to fit in the same box as everyone else. That imaginary box will suffocate you. Your journey is on another path. It’s not too late. It has its own perfect timing. You ARE your own timeline. Never too late. Never too early. Just in time.
You don't have to explain yourself to anyone, especially when it comes to why you do what you do and when you do it. You are alone accountable for your conduct. Your choices. It is your decision to begin. You make the decision to give it your all. It is your decision when a change is needed to. 
Be aware of the tendency to measure yourself by others’ standards. That only takes you further away from yourself, and it breeds self-judgment and shame.
When you accept that you are always moving forward, either expanding or learning, you will recognize that you are exactly where you need to be.
